(# Project Report: StudentHub Dashboard) Tj
T*
(## 1. Project Summary) Tj
T*
(StudentHub Dashboard is a frontend academic dashboard prototype built with React, Vite, and) Tj
T*
(Tailwind CSS. It provides a modern student portal experience for managing coursework,) Tj
T*
(attendance, grades, timetable, and profile settings.) Tj
T*
(## 2. Objectives) Tj
T*
(- Deliver a clean and responsive UI/UX for student workflows.) Tj
T*
(- Simulate a realistic academic dashboard without backend dependency.) Tj
T*
(- Provide modular components and maintainable project structure.) Tj
T*
(## 3. Tech Stack) Tj
T*
(- React 19) Tj
T*
(- Vite 7) Tj
T*
(- Tailwind CSS 3) Tj
T*
(- PostCSS + Autoprefixer) Tj
T*
(- Lucide React) Tj
T*
(## 4. Core Features) Tj
T*
(- Authentication flow with sign in/sign up and demo login.) Tj
T*
(- Dashboard with academic summary cards.) Tj
T*
(- Pages for assignments, lab sessions, timetable, exams, grades, progress tracking,) Tj
T*
(notifications, and settings.) Tj
T*
(- Local persistence for session and UI preferences using localStorage.) Tj
T*
(- UX improvements such as skeleton loading, toasts, modals, and error boundaries.) Tj
T*
(## 5. Architecture Overview) Tj
T*
(- `src/components/common`: Reusable UI elements.) Tj
T*
(- `src/components/layout`: Layout shell and route rendering.) Tj
T*
(- `src/pages`: Screen-level views for major modules.) Tj
T*
(- `src/services`: Mock API and auth/session storage.) Tj
T*
(- `src/context`: Global state management.) Tj
T*
(- `src/constants` and `src/data`: Config and mock data.) Tj
T*
(## 6. Current Status) Tj
T*
(- Frontend prototype is functional and build-ready.) Tj
T*
(- Production bundle generation succeeds via `npm run build`.) Tj
T*
(- Backend integration and automated testing are planned future steps.) Tj
T*
(## 7. Future Enhancements) Tj
T*
(- Integrate a real backend and persistent database.) Tj
T*
(- Add unit/integration test coverage.) Tj
T*
(- Introduce deep-link routing and API-backed widgets.) Tj
T*
(- Improve performance through code splitting and bundle optimization.) Tj
T*
(## 8. Conclusion) Tj
T*
(The StudentHub Dashboard successfully demonstrates a polished UI/UX mini project with) Tj
T*
(practical academic workflows and a strong foundation for future full-stack expansion.) Tj
ET
